Phoenix police are investigating an inquest case after a 30-year-old man was found hanged from a tree on Longbury Drive, last Monday night. Communications officer at Phoenix SAPS, Cpt Louise Naidoo, said the man hanged himself with his shirt. “The deceased has been identified and his next of kin was informed. There were no other injuries noted on the deceased. He was transported to Phoenix Mortuary,” said Cpt Naidoo.